{"lemma":"مَدَرَةُ","slug":"مَدَرَةُ","root":"م.د.ر","root_slug":"م-د-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/م-د-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12344","n12498","n38339","n38343"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُدِرّ (mudirr)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goat's rue (Galega officinalis), and other Galega legumes"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clod of loam or clay","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of مُرْدِيّ (murdiyy, “setting pole”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative","dialectal"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From أَدَرَّ (ʔadarra, “to let flow”), meaning in the participle also diuretic properties, and Galega officinalis is diuretic."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12344","headword_ar":"مِدَرَّةٌ","root":"dr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dar~aArapN","text_ar":"دَرَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12498","headword_ar":"مِدْرَهٌ","root":"drh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K;) so called because he is strong to execute affairs, and ventures upon them suddenly: (ISd, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a headman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqad~am","text_ar":"مُقَدَّم"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the copies of the K, but the right reading is probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqodim","text_ar":"مُقْدِم"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of tongue, on the occasion of contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disputation; and in arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand, on the occasion of fight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headman and spokesman"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or party: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spokesman and defender"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or party: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midorahu qawomK","text_ar":"مِدْرَهُ قَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the defender of a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headman, among them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the headman and orator and spokesman and defender of a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midorahu HarobK","text_ar":"مِدْرَهُ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same; (JK, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chief by whom evil is repelled, and who orders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arranges, the affairs of war:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 232:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaArihu","text_ar":"مَدَارِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["ISd","TA","S","Msb","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n38339","headword_ar":"مَدَرَهُ","root":"mdr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorN","text_ar":"مَدْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He plastered it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a place)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madar","text_ar":"مَدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"md~rhu","text_ar":"مدّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamodiyrN","text_ar":"تَمْدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repaired it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely a watering-trough or tank)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madar","text_ar":"مَدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he closed the interstices of its stones with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madar","text_ar":"مَدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he plastered its surface with clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud, in which was no sand, in order that it might not cleave open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that its water might not issue forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","M"]},{"entry_id":"n38343","headword_ar":"مَدَرَةٌ","root":"mdr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madarN","text_ar":"مَدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}